{
  "stem": "11723.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And that night we arrived at a place that was provided by a Protestant pastor's home.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And that was-- his name was Stelo.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "The pastor's name is Stelo.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "And he was another righteous Christian.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "He was helping Jewish boys live through this utter madness by providing them with food and everything in his house and also manufacturing forged papers for them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And hiding Jews was very dangerous to the person who committed such a crime.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And not only was it punishable by prison, maybe death, but it was more difficult to hide boys because of the circumcision problem.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "Anyway, we arrived there and he said he had a full house, but because it's a snowstorm we could spend the night.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "But he has no cots or anything, no beds.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "We'd have to sleep on the floor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And we said that's fine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "They had very little food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "I remember that we got three or four stalks of asparagus, canned asparagus, for dinner.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "And then again for breakfast.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "As long as I was there it was asparagus, and I never wanted to eat asparagus again until about 10 years ago.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "Anyway, so that night we spent in a room, sleeping on the floor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "I couldn't sleep all night because my mother was there and I was talking to her all night.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "And she told me that she came across the Danube.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "There were no bridges.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "The bridges were all-- well, they blew them up so that the Russians can't come across that way.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "The Nazi blew the bridges up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "And so my mother already was liberated.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "This is after Pest was already liberated, but Buda was not yet liberated.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "The Russians had not won that side of the city yet.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
